metadata.name: Entanglement #209
metadata.description:
This work contains a singular flow field that is directly influencing both the background radiation of particles and the formation of each nebula. Among many differences, the primary thing that separates them is the magnitude of that flow field.

Have a happy rebirth.

metadata.name: Solitude Meditation #6
metadata.description:
"A room, a space, a solitude corner within the inner thought. Existed as a place to meditate and replenish the soul to be more at ease."

This piece means to mimic a sense of a dark room that contains radiated warm lights with subtle movement. It will follow the current resolution of the window where it is placed.

/////INTERACTIVITY/////
Do all the instructions below after opening the live mode.

1. To capture the screen, press the "c" button on your computer keyboard.

2. To save a 3-second .GIF from your iteration, press the "s" button on your computer keyboard. Please be patient while waiting for the piece to save and render its frames.

3. To adjust the piece resolution, you need to set your browser first and then reload the browser every time you want to capture the screen or save the rendered .GIF file.
///////////////////////

Created using Hydra and p5.js

Rangga Purnama Aji, 2022
https://linktr.ee/ranggapuraji

metadata.name: Unstable Space #26
metadata.description:
The piece interprets the imaginary senses of an unstable space, where various disruptions might happen within its existence.

Inspired by the human tendency to need a private safe space but instead always faces a contradiction with reality. All are accumulated and abstracted into moving visual representations.
______________________________________________________________

///INTERACTIVITY///
Read the instructions below and do it after opening the live mode.

1. Press the "c" button on your computer keyboard to save a frame from your minted iteration.

2. To save a 3-second & 30 fps .GIF file, press the "s" button on your computer keyboard. Please be patient while waiting for the piece to save and render its frames.

3. The animated visual will always behave following the screen's resolution (e.g. the visual on 1:1 view and the live mode will show differently, but still give the same impression of the minted iteration). To adjust the piece resolution, you need to set your browser first and then reload the browser every time you want to capture the screen or save the rendered .GIFs file.

metadata.name: Negative Space #3
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: rive #271
metadata.description:
Starting with a repeatable system of colors and/or triangles typically seen in geometric abstraction, rive employs generative art to break/split/rive those patternsand the comfort we find in themin slight, seemingly unintentional ways.  With each subsequent split, our comfort fades as the artwork is shredded into barely recognizable fragments of a once carefully orchestrated pattern.

Not all rivings are created equal; some are subtle and barely visible while others are acute and violent.  

What holds it together is what breaks it apart.  

created using triangles and p5js

rive
abstractment, 2022

___________________________

Functionality:
Press p to save as a png.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality. 0 to 9 (highest quality, ~15k x ~15k, depending on the dimensions).  The window background will change colors when completed rendering.
Press  (arrow up) to increase pixel density by 0.5.
Press  (arrow down) to decrease pixel density by 0.5.

metadata.name: CHX-1 #170
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like its 1999.

Inspired by 90s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them individually and as a group with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN > p5js > Blockchain


 Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

 Press s (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of Franois Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
